
# ChartElegance PRD Document

## 1. Overview
ChartElegance is a sophisticated data visualization dashboard that transforms raw data into beautiful, interactive charts with elegant animations and customizable styling options.

## 2. Product Objectives
- Provide users with a visually stunning charting experience
- Support multiple chart types (line, bar, pie, scatter, etc.)
- Enable real-time data updates and smooth transitions
- Offer extensive customization options for design-conscious users

## 3. Features & Functionality

### 3.1 Core Visualization Features
- **Chart Gallery**: 
  - Line charts with smooth Bezier curves
  - 3D-rendered bar charts with adjustable lighting
  - Donut charts with interactive segment highlighting
  - Heatmaps with gradient color scaling
  - Radar charts with polygon fill effects

- **Animation System**:
  - Entry animations (fade, slide, bounce)
  - Data update transitions (morphing, interpolation)
  - Hover effects (glow, elevation, tooltip fade-in)

### 3.2 Data Handling
- JSON/CSV data import
- API endpoint connectivity
- Client-side data aggregation
- Real-time streaming support via WebSockets

### 3.3 Customization Options
- **Theme Engine**:
  - 10+ preset color palettes
  - Custom gradient builder
  - Dark/light mode switching

- **Style Controls**:
  - Axis styling (width, color, labels)
  - Data point markers (shapes, sizes)
  - Font selector with Google Fonts integration

### 3.4 Interactive Elements
- Zoom/pan functionality
- Data point inspection
- Series visibility toggles
- Export as PNG/SVG/PDF

## 4. Technical Specifications

### 4.1 Architecture
- Frontend: React + D3.js + Three.js
- Responsive design with mobile-first approach
- WebGL acceleration for complex visualizations

### 4.2 Performance
- 60fps rendering target
- Virtualized rendering for large datasets
- Web Worker support for data processing

## 5. UI/UX Requirements

### 5.1 Layout
- Main canvas area (70% width)
- Control panel (30% width, collapsible)
- Floating action buttons for common operations

### 5.2 States
- Loading state (animated skeleton)
- Empty state (illustration + CTA)
- Error state (clear messaging)

## 6. Success Metrics
- 95%+ rendering success rate
- <500ms initial load time
- 85%+ user satisfaction with visual quality

## 7. Future Roadmap
- Augmented reality view
- Collaborative editing
- AI-powered chart suggestions
- Plugin system for custom chart types
